---
import SEOLayout from '@layouts/SEOLayout.astro';
import Header from '@components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '@components/Footer.astro';
import Badge from '@components/Badge.astro';
import Card from '@components/Card.astro';
import Button from '@components/Button.astro';
import Divider from '@components/Divider.astro';
---

<SEOLayout
  title="Design Tokens: A Complete Guide"
  description="Understanding and customizing the SCSS design token system in this starter kit for consistent, maintainable design."
  type="article"
  publishedTime="2026-01-29T10:00:00Z"
  author="Author Name"
>
  <Header slot="header" siteName="Astro Starter Kit" />
  
  <article class="prose section-spacing">
    <div class="text-center">
      <div class="flex gap-2 justify-center mb-4">
        <Badge variant="success">Design</Badge>
        <Badge variant="default">SCSS</Badge>
      </div>
      
      <h1 class="hero-title">Design Tokens: A Complete Guide</h1>
      
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center mt-4 text-sm text-muted">
        <span>By Author Name</span>
        <span>•</span>
        <span>January 29, 2026</span>
        <span>•</span>
        <span>8 min read</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="stack mt-10">
      <p class="lead">
        Design tokens are the foundation of a scalable design system. This starter kit includes a comprehensive 
        token system for colors, spacing, typography, and more—all easily customizable.
      </p>

      <h2>What Are Design Tokens?</h2>
      <p>
        Design tokens are named entities that store visual design attributes. Instead of hardcoding values like 
        <code>#d4af37</code> or <code>16px</code>, 
        you use semantic names like <code>var(--accent)</code> or <code>var(--space-4)</code>.
      </p>

      <Card variant="bordered" padding="lg">
        <h3>Benefits of Design Tokens</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Consistency</strong> - Same values used everywhere</li>
          <li><strong>Maintainability</strong> - Update once, change everywhere</li>
          <li><strong>Scalability</strong> - Easy to add themes or variations</li>
          <li><strong>Communication</strong> - Shared language between design and dev</li>
        </ul>
      </Card>

      <h2>Token Categories</h2>
      <p>
        This starter organizes tokens into logical categories in the <code>src/styles/_tokens/</code> directory:
      </p>

      <h3>Colors</h3>
      <p>Color tokens in <code>_colors.scss</code>:</p>
      <Card variant="elevated" padding="md">
        <div class="grid grid--cols-2 gap-3 mt-3">
          <div class="p-3">
            <code>--bg</code>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3">
            <code>--bg-muted</code>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3">
            <code>--bg-elevated</code>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3">
            <code>--accent</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </Card>

      <Divider spacing="md" />

      <h3>Spacing</h3>
      <p>A consistent spacing scale in <code>_spacing.scss</code>:</p>
      <Card variant="elevated" padding="md">
        <div class="stack stack--gap-sm mt-3">
          <div class="flex align-center gap-3">
            <code class="text-sm">--space-1</code>
            <span class="text-sm text-muted">4px</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex align-center gap-3">
            <code class="text-sm">--space-4</code>
            <span class="text-sm text-muted">16px</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex align-center gap-3">
            <code class="text-sm">--space-8</code>
            <span class="text-sm text-muted">64px</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </Card>

      <Divider spacing="md" />

      <h3>Typography</h3>
      <p>Font sizes, weights, and line heights:</p>
      <Card variant="elevated" padding="md">
        <div class="mt-3">
          <p class="text-xs mb-2"><code>--text-xs</code> - Extra small text</p>
          <p class="text-sm mb-2"><code>--text-sm</code> - Small text</p>
          <p class="mb-2"><code>--text-base</code> - Base text</p>
          <p class="text-lg mb-2"><code>--text-lg</code> - Large text</p>
          <p class="text-xl mb-2"><code>--text-xl</code> - Extra large text</p>
        </div>
      </Card>

      <h2>Customizing Tokens</h2>
      <p>
        To customize tokens for your brand, edit the files in <code>src/styles/_tokens/</code>. 
        Changes will automatically propagate throughout the entire application.
      </p>

      <Card variant="bordered" padding="lg">
        <h4>Example: Changing Brand Colors</h4>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm">
          Edit <code>src/styles/_tokens/_colors.scss</code>:
        </p>
        <pre class="mt-3"><code>{`:root {
  --accent: #3b82f6; /* Change to your brand color */
  --accent-hover: #2563eb;
}`}</code></pre>
      </Card>

      <h2>Using Tokens in Your Code</h2>
      <p>
        Reference tokens using CSS custom properties in your SCSS files:
      </p>
      <pre><code>{`.my-element {
  padding: var(--space-4);
  color: var(--accent);
}`}</code></pre>

      <div class="flex gap-4 mt-8">
        <a href="/blog/getting-started">
          <Button variant="outline">← Previous: Getting Started</Button>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/seo-best-practices">
          <Button variant="primary">Next: SEO Best Practices →</Button>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
  
  <Footer slot="footer" siteName="Astro Starter Kit" />
</SEOLayout>
